  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 1, 1867, p. 1092: "Duris, of Elaea in Aeolis,
    the author of an epigram in the Greek Anthology (ii. 59, Brunck and Jacobs) on the inundation of Ephesus, which happened in the time of Lysimachus....."</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Epigrammatic poet from Elea (in Aeolis)
    author of a remarkable poem on the flood that destroyed Ephesus c. 300 BC (Anth. Pal. 9,424, cf. Steph. Byz. 289,3-16), 
    in all probability from the ‘Garland’ of Meleager...."</mads:note>
